  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "M&E Coordinator",
  "description": "<p><strong>Responsibilities:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Understand main contract and sub-contract requirements</li>\n  <li>Review and align M&amp;E design drawings to ensure compliance with specification and guidelines</li>\n  <li>Prepare combine services drawings and liaise with consultants / clients</li>\n  <li>Manage M&amp;E sub-contractors work progress, drawings, materials, samples, method statements submission and approval</li>\n  <li>Study, coordinate and supervise the M&amp;E works with client’s representatives, consultants and sub-contractors on technical matters</li>\n  <li>Ensure M&amp;E works are carried out according to specifications / drawings</li>\n  <li>Ensure M&amp;E works are performing on time, within budget and in compliance with all necessary standards, code of practice and safety regulations</li>\n  <li>Attend site meeting as and when required</li>\n  <li>Any other ad-hoc tasks assigned by the Management</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Requirements:</strong></p>\n<p>· Degree / Diploma in Mechanical / Electrical Engineering and / or Specialist Diploma in M&amp;E Coordination will be an advantage, recognised by local authority.</p>\n<p>· Min 2 years or more experience as M&amp;E Coordinator in local construction firm with Facility Management experience.</p>\n<p>· Good knowledge in Singapore standards &amp; requirements</p>\n<p>· Able to work independently with positive attitude</p>\n<p>· Good communication and interpersonal skills</p>",
